OL,3,CFree abortions 'risks' them being form
OL,4,Cof contraception, health boss says
OL,6,F"It was a fairly alarming statement,"
OL,7,Fshe said. "Shortly after the meeting,
OL,8,FI did some fact-checking and couldn't
OL,9,Ffind any firm research pointing to
OL,10,Fwomen deciding they want to use
OL,11,Ftermination as contraception.
OL,13,F"I did find some sociological evidence
OL,14,Fthat sometimes women are forced to do
OL,15,Fso through circumstances where they
OL,16,Fcan't access or afford contraception,
OL,17,Ffor example, if they are victims of
OL,18,Fabuse or living in poverty.
