OL,3,CFree abortions 'risks' them being form
OL,4,Cof contraception, health boss says
OL,6,FDr Caroline Mair, who specialises in
OL,7,Fgynaecology and family planning, does
OL,8,Fnot believe that cost plays a
OL,9,Fsignificant role in women's decisions
OL,10,Fto have their pregnancies terminated.
OL,12,F"I'm confident in saying that I don't
OL,13,Fthink making abortion free would ever
OL,14,Fbe a threat to sensible, safe
OL,15,Fcontraception," she explained.
OL,17,F"It's not a pleasant procedure to have
OL,18,Fto go through; there are risks
OL,19,Fassociated with abortions, which can
OL,20,Fhave clinical and psychological
OL,21,Fconsequences.
